{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/socketref\/set(keepalive:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"keepalive","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"extendedModule":"GIO","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO14SocketProtocolPAAE3set9keepaliveySb_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO9SocketRefV","role":"symbol","title":"set(keepalive:)"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef\/set(keepalive:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets or unsets the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SO_KEEPALIVE"},{"type":"text","text":" flag on the underlying socket. When"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this flag is set on a socket, the system will attempt to verify that the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remote socket endpoint is still present if a sufficiently long period of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time passes with no data being exchanged. If the system is unable to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"verify the presence of the remote endpoint, it will automatically close"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the connection."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"keepalive","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This option is only functional on certain kinds of sockets. (Notably,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"tcp","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" sockets.)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The exact time between pings is system- and protocol-dependent, but will","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"normally be at least two hours. Most commonly, you would set this flag"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on a server socket if you want to allow clients to remain idle for long","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"periods of time, but also want to ensure that connections are eventually"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"garbage-collected if clients crash or become unreachable.","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef\/SocketProtocol-Implementations"]]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketRef/SocketProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"SocketProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketref\/socketprotocol-implementations","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef\/SocketProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketRef/set(keepalive:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef\/set(keepalive:)","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Sets or unsets the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SO_KEEPALIVE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag on the underlying socket. When","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this flag is set on a socket, the system will attempt to verify that the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"remote socket endpoint is still present if a sufficiently long period of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time passes with no data being exchanged. If the system is unable to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"verify the presence of the remote endpoint, it will automatically close","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the connection.","type":"text"}],"title":"set(keepalive:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketref\/set(keepalive:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"keepalive","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketRef":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef","title":"SocketRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketref","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a low-level networking primitive. It is a more or less"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"direct mapping of the BSD socket API in a portable GObject based API.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It supports both the UNIX socket implementations and winsock2 on Windows.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketRef","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SocketRef","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"}}}